According to Fox 26, the girls' mother, Barbara Russo, their uncle and their older brother were home when the incident occurred. 

Both girls were rushed by Life Flight medical helicopter to Memorial Hermann Children's Hospital after their mother called 911.

It is still not known just how long the two girls were underwater.  

'My heart goes out to the family. I know that they're grieving,' said Judy Poston, one of the family's neighbors.

'The baby had very little brain activity so she's better off where she is.' 

Poston also said the Russo told her she was able to give Sabrina CPR after finding her in the tub.

A purple butterfly in memory of the girls hung on a tree outside the house

