According to KHOU, the parents had recently split, but were now back together.

They also said the family kept to themselves, with one neighbor describing them as 'just not your typical "can I borrow some sugar from you" kind of neighbor.'

Children's Protective Services is also investigating the incident, and said they had been involved with the family before and the older child, who is three-years-old.

He has been removed from the home and is now with family friends. 

'I hope that they can get through this together. I hope that eventually they can become strong. I know that you never ever get over the death of a child but with time hopefully they can get on with their lives,' said Poston. 

'It's very sad, not one baby, but two,' said Lene Owerbach, another neighbor. 

'I don't even know what to think it's going to be with them the rest of their lives. It must be devastating to them.'

